                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1384">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/225.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Letcher</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul Hamra now at Torreon telegraphs that a great many flagrant cases of
                    confiscation of abandoned Spanish property have already occurred at Torreon and
                    vicinity. In view of General Carranza’s published statement in the press a few
                    days ago to the effect that Spanish property at Torreon would not be molested,
                    you will please call the Torreon situation to Carranza’s attention and endeavor
                    to secure a definite expression from him as to what may be expected regarding
                    the abandoned property of Spanish subjects at Torreon and what steps will be
                    taken to secure the protection of this property and the punishment of those
                    guilty of looting and confiscating Spanish property.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
